ch as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":6,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Gamage was born in 1284, in Nunney, Somerset, England. She had at least 2 sons with Thomas de la Mare. She died in 1305, in her hometown, at the age of 21."},"et":{"1284–1305":"1284–1305","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1296–1388":"1296–1388","1302–Male":"1302–Surnud","1305":"1305","1302":"1302","1388":"1388","1296":"1296","about 1302":"umbes 1302","1284":"1284","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","Nunney, Somerset, England":"Nunney, Somerset, England","Nunney, Frome, Somerset, England":"Nunney, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1284–1305":"1284–1305","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1296–1388":"1296–1388","1302–Male":"1302–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1302":"1302","1388":"1388","1296":"1296","about 1302":"noin 1302","1284":"1284","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","Nunney, Somerset, England":"Nunney, Somerset, England","Nunney, Frome, Somerset, England":"Nunney, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1284–1305":"1284–1305","1280–Male":"1280–Décédé","1296–1388":"1296–1388","1302–Male":"1302–Décédé","1305":"1305","1302":"1302","1388":"1388","1296":"1296","about 1302":"environ 